#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:2
msgid "Flakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:4
msgid "What are flakes?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:6
msgid ""
"Flakes offer an entrypoint file `flake.nix` aimed at sharing Nix code. They "
"make it easy to build programs with the same version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:9
msgid ""
"`flake.nix` is a file that declares inputs and outputs with a [standard "
"structure]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:11
msgid "Note: [Experimental], requires [Nix 2.4]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:13
msgid "This file can look like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:15
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  description = \"My example flake\";\n"
"\n"
"  inputs = {\n"
"    nixpkgs.url = \"github:nixos/nixpkgs?ref=nixos-unstable\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  outputs = { self, nixpkgs }: {\n"
"    packages.x86_64-linux = {\n"
"      default = self.packages.x86_64-linux.hello;\n"
"      hello = nixpkgs.legacyPackages.x86_64-linux.hello;\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:32
msgid ""
"[`outputs`] include various [built-in types], but can be [extended]. You can "
"find an overview of these on the [wiki]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:35
msgid "[`inputs`] let you declare dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:37
msgid ""
"Nix creates a [`flake.lock`] to pin dependencies once you run a [`nix` "
"command]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:39
msgid ""
"If these dependencies have `inputs` of their own, Nix will check _their_ "
"lock files to find the versions to use. Using the same versions helps make "
"sure programs work as intended, but you can override these."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:42
msgid "[`nix` command]s natively integrate with flakes by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:44
msgid "nix build github:NixOS/nixpkgs#hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:48
msgid ""
"You may pass [references] to local (e.g. `.`) or remote (e.g. `github:NixOS/"
"nixpkgs`) project directories. For further details see the reference on "
"[`nix` command]s."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:51
msgid ""
"Aliases to flakes are stored in a [registry]. This can be extended by "
"[command-line] or by {term}`NixOS` option [`nix.registry`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:60
msgid "The NixOS manual further explains [flake-based installs]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:80
msgid "Should I use flakes in my project?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:82
msgid ""
"Flakes are an experimental extension format with outstanding issues. Its "
"functionality can generally be achieved without them as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:85
msgid ""
"If you need to run existing software that already used flakes, or want to "
"contribute to their development, feel free to use them. If you want to write "
"Nix code yourself, consider also our guide on [dependency management]."
"[^flake-inputs] This overview can help get what you need from flakes while "
"preserving compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:93
msgid "Discoverability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:95
msgid ""
"A first step in use of flakes is to add a `flake.nix` file specifying "
"`outputs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:97 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:166
#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:238 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:269
msgid "Pros:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:99
msgid "Use the code from other flake projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:100
msgid "Nix checks `flake.nix`'s structure is valid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:102 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:182
#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:243 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:273
msgid "Cons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:104
msgid ""
"Flakes have no [parameters]. This means `flake.nix` and its end-user must be "
"explicit about the used [`system`]. This is made easier by say [`flake-"
"utils`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:107
msgid "As an experimental feature, flakes can still change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:113 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:193
#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:253 ../../../concepts/flakes.md:277
msgid "Alternatives:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:115
msgid ""
"Use flakes as thin wrappers over existing Nix code. This way, code can be "
"used in both ways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:117
msgid "Use Nix modules: flake users can import these with `flake = false;`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:121
msgid "Running commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:123
msgid ""
"Flakes are used from Nix's [v3 `nix` command line interface]. It can build "
"or run programs by a reference like `.` or `github:NixOS/nixpkgs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:126
msgid "You can enable this for one command by adding:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:128
msgid " --experimental-features 'nix-command flakes'\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:132
msgid "Or permanently in NixOS or Home Manager configurations using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:134
msgid "nix.settings.experimental-features = [ \"nix-command\" \"flakes\" ];\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:138
msgid ""
"To build the derivation in your `flake.nix`'s `packages.x86_64-linux."
"default`, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:140
msgid "nix build .#packages.x86_64-linux.default\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:144
msgid "You can shorten this to `nix build .#default`, or just `nix build`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:146
msgid ""
"`nix run` runs programs in `outputs.apps`. `nix run .#default` runs `outputs."
"apps.default`. Just `nix run` also runs that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:150
msgid "For example, to run the `hello` package from {term}`Nixpkgs`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:152
msgid "nix run nixpkgs#hello -- --greeting \"hello from flakes\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:156
msgid "This uses the version set by your registry's alias `nixpkgs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:158
msgid ""
"To run the `hello` package from {term}`Nixpkgs`' `nixpkgs-unstable` branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:160
msgid "nix run github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixpkgs-unstable#hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:168
msgid ""
"Flakes cache builds to save time on later identical builds. This can save "
"time if you run unchanged builds in Continuous Integration, for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:170
msgid ""
"Flakes promote making programs easy to run, also from remote repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:171
msgid ""
"Flakes default to running in [pure mode]. This promotes a style of writing "
"programs more likely to make them reproducible[^reproducible]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:173
msgid ""
"Flakes build only tracked files, for projects using [Git]. This helps "
"prevent rebuilds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:184
msgid ""
"Builds copy the whole flake directory to the Nix store. This caches them, "
"but can be [slower] for large repositories like {term}`Nixpkgs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:186
msgid "The implementation still has issues for both [flakes] and the [v3 CLI]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:187
msgid "Files must be staged for flakes to see them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:195
msgid ""
"Plain Nix files can be used with the [v2 commands] (like [`nix-build`], "
"[`nix-shell`]), or with v3 commands' [`--file` flag] or `-f`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:196
msgid ""
"In {term}`NixOS`, you can make v3 commands' `nixpkgs` to a package set "
"`pkgs` by setting [`nixpkgs.flake.source = pkgs.path;`] in your NixOS "
"configuration. Also see [managing dependencies]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:198
msgid ""
"Using [`builtins.fetchTree`] from experimental feature [`fetch-tree`], [`nix "
"run`] may be emulated[^emulated] for non-flake entrypoints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:214
msgid "Dependency management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:216
msgid ""
"Flakes' `inputs` attribute can manage dependencies. By default this handles "
"recursive dependencies implicitly. In case a library is used multiple times, "
"this can give different versions of the same library. You can override these "
"if you want using `follows` statements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:221
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  inputs = {\n"
"    nixpkgs.url = \"github:nixos/nixpkgs?ref=nixos-unstable\";\n"
"    home-manager = {\n"
"      url = \"github:nix-community/home-manager\";\n"
"      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = \"nixpkgs\";\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:233
msgid "This way, Home Manager's inputs reuse your chosen `nixpkgs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:235
msgid ""
"If you don't want to load a dependency, you can also disable it. In the "
"above example, that could look like `inputs.home-manager.inputs.nixpkgs = "
"null;`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:240
msgid ""
"Make it easy to reproduce published software, following the versions they "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:241
msgid "You can override recursive inputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:245
msgid ""
"Flakes by default follow versions from dependencies' `flake.lock`, so if you "
"don't override these with `follows`, you may get:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:246
msgid "multiple versions of the same dependency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:247
msgid "outdated dependencies, if their versions are not actively updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:248
msgid "Dependencies are fetched eagerly, loading dependencies you may not use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:249
msgid ""
"Dependencies managed by flake inputs are hard to override if you don't also "
"use flakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:250
msgid ""
"If your flake is used as a library, you need to add `follows` statements for "
"all recursive inputs. Otherwise downstream consumers cannot add their "
"`follows` on your indirect inputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:255
msgid "Handle dependencies with [`npins`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:256
msgid ""
"Handle dependencies inline using functions such as the [fetchers] or "
"[`builtins.fetchTree`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:262
msgid "Flake-only Nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:264
msgid ""
"As flakes (largely[^subset]) use Nix as an internal language, you could even "
"place all Nix code in flake files. In the community, such a coding style is "
"called dendritic pattern. Using flakes, this pattern gets easier with "
"library [`flake-parts`](https://github.com/hercules-ci/flake-parts), which "
"lets you spread code over different flake-like files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:271
msgid "Helps use flakes' schema and inputs from any such Nix code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:275
msgid "Makes it harder to access this code without using flakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:279
msgid ""
"Use flakes as thin wrappers over existing Nix code, so code can be used in "
"both ways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:280
msgid ""
"Use library [`flake-compat`] to expose a flake's default package or shell to "
"non-flake users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:281
msgid ""
"Propagate needed parameters across modules explicitly or with NixOS's "
"[`specialArgs`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:286
msgid "History"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:288
msgid "Conception"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:289
msgid "Flakes were proposed in [RFC 49], and introduced in a [blog post]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:290
msgid "Design"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:291
msgid ""
"The flakes proposal was criticised for trying to solve too many problems at "
"once and at the wrong abstraction layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:292
msgid ""
"The design still has [various problems] including around versioning, "
"composability, cross-compilation, and tight coupling with nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:293
msgid "There are also still many [open design questions] around the `nix` CLI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:294
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:295
msgid "There are still [problems with the implementation]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:296
msgid "Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:297
msgid ""
"While there were still outstanding concerns about the design, the "
"implementation was merged without the RFC having been accepted (and in fact "
"being withdrawn on merge), raising questions about proper process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:300
msgid "The RFC was closed with no timeline to conclude the experiment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:301
msgid ""
"Flakes had become depended on by many projects, making it harder to iterate "
"on their design without breaking many people's code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:302
msgid "Community"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:303
msgid ""
"The design had not been accepted by all parts of the community, with e.g. "
"{term}`Nixpkgs` not using it in its internal tooling. As a result of this, "
"branching approaches to flakes have been made, with e.g. company Determinate "
"Systems (which offers proprietary features around flakes) unilaterally "
"declaring the feature stable, while community-driven Nix fork Lix "
"[consolidated the featureset] to a de-facto 'v1'. Such branching could "
"potentially end up breaking the promise of a unified interface that "
"propelled the flakes experiment in the first place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:316
msgid "Further reading"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:318
msgid "[wiki article](https://wiki.nixos.org/wiki/Flakes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:319
msgid ""
"[Flakes aren't real and cannot hurt you: a guide to using Nix flakes the non-"
"flake way](https://jade.fyi/blog/flakes-arent-real/) (Jade Lovelace, January "
"2024)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:320
msgid ""
"[Nix Flakes is an experiment that did too much at once...](https://samuel."
"dionne-riel.com/blog/2023/09/06/flakes-is-an-experiment-that-did-too-much-at-"
"once.html) ([comments](https://discourse.nixos.org/t/nix-flakes-is-an-"
"experiment-that-did-too-much-at-once/32707)) (Samuel Dionne-Riel, September "
"2023)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:321
msgid ""
"[Experimental does not mean unstable](https://determinate.systems/posts/"
"experimental-does-not-mean-unstable) ([comments](https://discourse.nixos.org/"
"t/experimental-does-not-mean-unstable-detsyss-perspective-on-nix-"
"flakes/32703)) (Graham Christensen, September 2023)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:322
msgid ""
"[The Nix Hour: comparing flakes to traditional Nix](https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v=atmoYyBAhF4) (Silvan Mosberger, November 2022)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:91
msgid ""
"Nix repositories offering only flake entrypoints may be imported using "
"[`flake-inputs`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:178
msgid "Even in pure mode, reproducibility is [not actually guaranteed]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:211
msgid ""
"`nix run github:NixOS/nixpkgs#hello` for non-flake projects may look like "
"`nix-shell -p '(import (builtins.fetchTree \"github:NixOS/nixpkgs\").outPath "
"{ }).hello' --run 'hello'`. A drop-in command `nix-run` using the `nix run` "
"syntax could be defined using a Bash alias like `alias nix-run='run() "
"{ $(nix-instantiate --raw --impure --eval --expr \"(import <nixpkgs> {}).lib."
"getExe (import (builtins.fetchTree \\\"$(cut -d \"#\" -f 1 <<< \"$1\")\\\")."
"outPath { }).$(cut -d \"#\" -f 2 <<< \"$1\")\"); }; run'`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/flakes.md:54
msgid ""
"Flakes default to pure mode, isolating builds from the host environment. "
"This is also called hermetic evaluation, and prevents evaluating (non-"
"network) [impure] functions. Flake `inputs` and metadata fields cannot be "
"arbitrary Nix expressions. This is to prevent complex, possibly non-"
"terminating computations. The `outputs` field's function parameter must be "
"specified: it does not support [eta-reduction]."
msgstr ""
